      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the belief that the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding of its authors and the people at the time it was written. Proponents argue that this approach maintains the rule of law, prevents judges from imposing their personal views, and respects the democratic process by adhering to the text as it was intended by the framers. They believe that this method preserves the Constitution's integrity and prevents judicial activism. Originalism also emphasizes that the Constitution is a stable, enduring document that should not be subject to the whims of changing societal values or political ideologies.",
