      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so basically it's about keeping things stable. but i've heard people say that originalism is actually just a way for judges to push a specific conservative agenda under the guise of law. how do scholars usually respond to the criticism that it's more of a political tool than a real legal theory?",
