      "content": "that makes sense, but i'm looking at some articles that say the whole idea of \"original meaning\" is basically impossible to pin down because the founders weren't a monolith. some people argue that originalism is actually just \"law office history\" where judges pick and choose whatever historical facts fit their desired outcome. do you think there's any merit to the idea that originalism is fundamentally flawed because it's just used to legitimize certain viewpoints?",
